Antenna (
Fig. 25
) with radicle about 4.5x as long as wide, rest of scape about 5.0x as long as wide, lightly striate; pedicel longer than F1; F2 longer than F1, F3–F8 subequal in length, F1–F4 slightly narrower than F5 or F6 and notably narrower than F7 or F8; F1–F4 without mps, F5 usually with but sometimes without 1 mps, F6 usually with 1 mps but sometimes without or with 2 mps, F7 and F8 each with 2 mps; clava with 8 mps, 3.0–3.3x as long as wide, slightly longer than combined length of F6–F8.

Metasoma (
Fig. 26
). Petiole short, a little wider than long, trapezoidal. Ovipositor 0.7–0.8x length of gaster, not or barely exserted beyond its apex; ovipositor length: mesotibia length ratio 0.9–1.0:1.
